00:00:01.965 --> 00:00:03.965
Some promoters of raw food diets claim

00:00:04.669 --> 00:00:06.669
that the "living" enzymes in plant foods

00:00:06.904 --> 00:00:08.904
are necessary for human digestion and health.

00:00:11.556 --> 00:00:13.556
They also claim that your body has only

00:00:13.036 --> 00:00:15.036
a finite supply of digestive enzymes

00:00:14.814 --> 00:00:16.814
so these enzymes from vegetables and fruit

00:00:16.388 --> 00:00:18.388
become more important as you age.

00:00:19.097 --> 00:00:21.097
They say that cooking denatures these live enzymes

00:00:21.647 --> 00:00:23.647
so that they cannot perform their function in the body.

00:00:25.846 --> 00:00:27.846
I would like to emphasize that only some raw food promoters

00:00:29.038 --> 00:00:31.038
make this claim.

00:00:30.323 --> 00:00:32.323
There are notable examples of those who will state 

00:00:32.023 --> 00:00:34.023
that this claim is not true.

00:00:34.323 --> 00:00:36.323
They may be in the minority, however,

00:00:35.528 --> 00:00:37.528
of those who actually follow such a diet. 

00:00:41.315 --> 00:00:43.315
Let's examine these claims.

00:00:44.586 --> 00:00:46.586
Do plant foods have enzymes? Yes.

00:00:46.840 --> 00:00:48.840
Are these plant enzymes active in human digestion? No.

00:00:50.836 --> 00:00:52.836
Plant enzymes are there for the plant to use.

00:00:53.265 --> 00:00:55.265
There is no evidence that they have any role 

00:00:55.236 --> 00:00:57.236
whatsoever in human health, 

00:00:56.824 --> 00:00:58.824
other than to provide a source of amino acids.

00:01:04.229 --> 00:01:06.229
Does cooking denature these enzymes? Yes.

00:01:08.467 --> 00:01:10.467
They are protein based and heat application will denature the proteins.

00:01:12.969 --> 00:01:14.969
To denature a protein means to change its shape 

00:01:15.562 --> 00:01:17.562
in such a way that it is not biologically active.

00:01:19.464 --> 00:01:21.464
What you may not know is that applying an acid

00:01:21.465 --> 00:01:23.465
to protein foods, does much the same thing as heat.

00:01:24.971 --> 00:01:26.971
This means that these protein enzymes will become denatured

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:30.000
in the harsh acidic environment of the stomach. 

00:01:31.038 --> 00:01:33.038
However, this does not effect their digestion 

00:01:33.161 --> 00:01:35.161
as peptides and amino acids.

00:01:34.993 --> 00:01:36.993
In fact, as far as protein goes,

00:01:37.608 --> 00:01:39.608
cooking them makes them somewhat more bio-available.

00:01:41.582 --> 00:01:43.580
This means that a larger percentage of the protein 

00:01:43.761 --> 00:01:45.760
can be successfully broken down and absorbed.

00:01:46.856 --> 00:01:48.860
The myth that denaturing proteins is bad for human health

00:01:46.856 --> 00:01:48.860
The myth that denaturing proteins is bad for human health

00:01:49.684 --> 00:01:51.680
is based on the idea that whole proteins

00:01:52.107 --> 00:01:54.110
are biologically active and can be absorbed by the body 

00:01:55.034 --> 00:01:57.030
to perform certain roles as proteins,

00:01:57.867 --> 00:01:59.870
as opposed to being broken down into amino acids

00:02:00.076 --> 00:02:02.080
to be made into other proteins by the body.

00:02:03.522 --> 00:02:05.520
We'll examine this next. 

00:02:10.196 --> 00:02:12.200
Can whole proteins be absorbed by the small intestine?

00:02:15.587 --> 00:02:17.590
Well, for the first few weeks after birth,

00:02:18.420 --> 00:02:20.420
 a newborn's small intestine absorbs

00:02:19.879 --> 00:02:21.880
a fairly good amount of intact proteins.

00:02:22.427 --> 00:02:24.430
For example, gamma globulin proteins present in mother's milk

00:02:26.361 --> 00:02:28.360
appear to be absorbed since the newborn has specific receptors

00:02:29.575 --> 00:02:31.580
for binding and transporting them.

00:02:31.925 --> 00:02:33.920
The stomach pH is lower 

00:02:33.406 --> 00:02:35.410
so that pepsin is not as active

00:02:35.005 --> 00:02:37.000
and there are trypsin inhibitors, 

00:02:36.514 --> 00:02:38.510
all of which helps keep the protein intact.

00:02:39.164 --> 00:02:41.160
This appears to be a way for the infant

00:02:40.962 --> 00:02:42.960
to receive active antibodies.

00:02:43.154 --> 00:02:45.150
Even so, we do not know how well 

00:02:45.325 --> 00:02:47.320
this mechanism works in human infants. 

00:02:47.428 --> 00:02:49.430
Only a very tiny amount 

00:02:49.031 --> 00:02:51.030
of intact protein is absorbed by adults

00:02:51.539 --> 00:02:53.540
and in certain people,

00:02:52.533 --> 00:02:54.530
ome of these proteins result in anyphylactic or hypersensitivity reactions.

00:02:56.404 --> 00:02:58.400
Other proteins may have a small role

00:02:58.985 --> 00:03:00.980
in gut health.

00:03:00.523 --> 00:03:02.520
However, to exaggerate the importance of this

00:03:02.782 --> 00:03:04.780
is to exaggerate something we know very little about.

