00:03:43.555 --> 00:03:45.560
First let's define an enzyme.

00:03:47.522 --> 00:03:49.520
An enzyme is a protein that facilitates chemical reactions 

00:03:49.396 --> 00:03:51.400
without itself being changed by the reaction.

00:03:52.390 --> 00:03:54.390
Enzymes are known as catalysts.

00:03:54.936 --> 00:03:56.940
The digestive enzymes are large proteins

00:03:56.552 --> 00:03:58.550
that facilitate a chemical reaction known as hydrolysis.

00:03:59.720 --> 00:04:01.720
Hydrolysis is the addition of water to break down

00:04:01.995 --> 00:04:04.000
a molecule into smaller pieces. 

00:04:04.718 --> 00:04:06.720
This happens to proteins, carbohydrates, and fats,

00:04:06.599 --> 00:04:08.600
each of which have certain enzymes to hydrolyze them.

00:04:10.429 --> 00:04:12.430
Enzymes are, of course, 

00:04:12.068 --> 00:04:14.070
not the only components of digestion,

00:04:13.846 --> 00:04:15.850
but our discussion will focus on them

00:04:15.407 --> 00:04:17.410
and not on the digestive process as a whole.

00:04:23.686 --> 00:04:25.690
